args:
Attention! Archbishop Bern reports
the Hillheim diocese is recruiting new
Templars! All current applicants
will be exempt from entrance
examinations. Enlist today!
Recruitin' Templars again? Weren't they\njust doing that in the Leppo district?
Cor, and without even an entrance exam!\nMight give it a shot m'self, just for the\nlaughs and a fine story.
Ha! You can't even lift a sword, mate!\nStill, it makes a fella wonder what\nthey need all the warm bodies for.
The bishop has no concept of true tactics.\nThose damnable perditionists are simply\nbecoming ever more desperate!
And so does the land of the goddess\nfall ever deeper into waste. If only\nHeavenwing Silvain were still alive...
One...two...one... *pant* P-Paladyn Tobias,\nsir? Exactly how long must we continue\nperforming practice swings?
You have 500 reps remaining—and I have\nother business to attend to. Be certain\nthey are done by the time I return.
He's no Paladyn, but a damn devil!
Aw, there's nothing more fun than training!\nBesides, what's 500 more?
My heart leapt in my chest when I heard new\napplicants were exempt from entrance exams,\nand now I spend every waking moment training!
And the best part? The person overseeing my\ntraining is a Paladyn! A true Paladyn! You better\nbelieve I won't throw away THIS chance...
One! Two! One...twoooo... Whew!\nI'm all kinds of tuckered, but it's worth\nit to make my dream come true.

My opinion on the matter has not changed,
Your Grace—I cannot advise further
thoughtless ballooning of our ranks
with these legions of new recruits.
Such new blood is as useless as a hat\non a fish without proper training.

And because of the manpower such
training requires, security in other
locations all across the land is now
sorely lacking.

I am aware you would have us make ready
for conflict with the conservatives, but
this current plan of action is placing
the cart well before the horse.

Your feelings are well understood, Tobias.
However, a great cause calls for extensive
preparation; we are merely sowing seeds
for harvest at a later date.
It is not one hero which determines the\ncurrent, but an army. I should think you\nunderstand that point as well as anyone?
I expect great things of you, Tobias.\nYou are, after all, his one and only child.
There you are, sir! Where were you?
Merely seeing to an errand, er... I'm sorry,\nare you one of the new Templar recruits?
Yes, sir! And the name's Hope, sir!\nAlso, I finished my 500 practice swings\nand was wondering what to work on next.
I see. Er, and where are your\nfellow recruits, if I may ask?
Collapsed on the ground, sir! They all\nsaid they couldn't take it anymore and\nstarting crying and... Well, other things.

From a mere 500 practice swings? Fie!
This is why we need a stringent entrance
exam instead of allowing any feckless
oaf to stumble through our door.
...But very well. Though you may be\nwithout any of your peers, I would still\ntake the measure of your strength. Come.
I'll give it my best, sir!
Hmm, about what I'd expect. Hardly\nimpressive, but there is potential there.\nYou'll improve with training.
Seriously?! Ehehehe... I knew it, maybe\nI'm just a naturally talented knight.
Heck, I knew I had the capacity\nto be more than just a priest!
Well, my first profession was in the\npriesthood, but now I'm studying\nto be both a priest AND a knight.
And why would a boy of the cloth harbor\nthe ambition to become a Templar?
Because I want to help people!
Er, not that priests aren't helpful, per se.\nI just want to help them DIFFERENTLY.
Also, I've always wanted to be a knight.
I mean, the more ways I have to help\npeople out, the better, I always say.
It's a dream I've had ever since I was\nsaved by a Heavenwing some years ago.
A Templar who is skilled in battle,\nhealing arts, AND a parish leader?\nI mean, what's better than that?!
Anyway, when I heard the Heavenwing\npost was vacant here, I figured I'd show\nup and give it my best shot.
The path of a Heavenwing is not some\ntrivial idea to be tossed about, boy!

You seem to mistake the knighthood for
some flashy existence. Helping people is
an act of great responsibility—something
which I am unsure you comprehend.
Would you truly navigate the path before\nyou with such a frivolous attitude?
Um, yes? I mean, er... Look, I know\nwhat you're saying, and I understand\nthis isn't going to be easy.
But I have more determination than\nanyone, so I know I can do it!
Whatever hardships I might face, my\nresolve and passion will see me through.
(I've seen that fearless look before.\nIt's the same one I once saw in my\nmaster's eyes...)

(Though I suppose his type can also grow
into... No. If this sprout has the potential to
grow strong, then now is not the time to be
selective.)

Enough, boy! All the gumption in the
world will not help a weak thing like you
become a Templar of even modest rank,
let alone a Heavenwing.
If you truly desire such a path for yourself,\nI must train you like you have never been\ntrained before. Are you prepared for this?
That's exactly what I was\nHOPING you would do, sir!
